{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. The issue asks me to: **After selecting a project, show its issues in the same list format as My Issues. Reuse list/detail components. Esc to go back to project list.**\n\nLooking at the current code, the project detail view (`ProjectDetail`) already exists with:\n1. A `project.rs` view that shows issues in a table\n2. Navigation (up/down/top/bottom) for project issues\n3. Esc to go back to project list\n\nHowever, what's missing is the ability to **select a project issue and view its detail** (like the `Detail` view for My Issues), and the **\"same list format as My Issues\"** means the project issue list should be able to open the issue detail view when Enter is pressed.\n\nLet me examine what happens when you select a project issue — currently in `main.rs`, the `ProjectDetail` view only has `MoveDown/MoveUp/Top/Bottom/Back/Refresh/Help` actions, but no `Select` action to open issue detail. Let me implement this.\n\nThe key changes needed:\n1. Add a `select_project_issue()` method to `App` that enters the `Detail` view\n2. Track which context we came from so `back_to_list` returns to the right view\n3. Handle `Select` action in the `ProjectDetail` key handler in `main.rs`\n4. Make `selected_issue()` work for project issues when in project context\n\nLet me look at how `selected_issue()` is used in the Detail view and main.rs more carefully:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_01KkfhCAUKrCLn3xLi9e8poM","name":"Read","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/views/help.rs"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2657,"cache_read_input_tokens":86559,"output_tokens":438,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01KkfhCAUKrCLn3xLi9e8poM","content":"{\"absolutePath\":\"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/views/help.rs\",\"content\":\"1: use ratatui::{\\n2:     layout::Rect,\\n3:     style::{Color, Modifier, Style},\\n4:     text::{Line, Span},\\n5:     widgets::{Block, Borders, Clear, Paragraph},\\n6:     Frame,\\n7: };\\n8: \\n9: /// All keybindings shown in the help overlay.\\n10: /// Each entry is (key_label, description).\\n11: pub const KEYBINDINGS: &[(&str, &str)] = &[\\n12:     (\\\"?\\\", \\\"Toggle this help\\\"),\\n13:     (\\\"q\\\", \\\"Quit (press twice)\\\"),\\n14:     (\\\"Ctrl+c\\\", \\\"Quit immediately\\\"),\\n15:     (\\\"j / ↓\\\", \\\"Move down / scroll down\\\"),\\n16:     (\\\"k / ↑\\\", \\\"Move up / scroll up\\\"),\\n17:     (\\\"g\\\", \\\"Go to top\\\"),\\n18:     (\\\"G\\\", \\\"Go to bottom\\\"),\\n19:     (\\\"Enter\\\", \\\"Select / confirm\\\"),\\n20:     (\\\"Esc\\\", \\\"Back / dismiss\\\"),\\n21:     (\\\"/\\\", \\\"Search\\\"),\\n22:     (\\\"s\\\", \\\"Sort by column\\\"),\\n23:     (\\\"f\\\", \\\"Filter by column\\\"),\\n24:     (\\\"r\\\", \\\"Refresh\\\"),\\n25:     (\\\"o\\\", \\\"Open in Linear / GitHub\\\"),\\n26:     (\\\"Tab\\\", \\\"Switch section (detail)\\\"),\\n27:     (\\\"a\\\", \\\"New Amp thread (detail)\\\"),\\n28:     (\\\"p\\\", \\\"Projects\\\"),\\n29: ];\\n30: \\n31: pub fn render(frame: &mut Frame, area: Rect) {\\n32:     let key_style = Style::default()\\n33:         .fg(Color::Yellow)\\n34:         .add_modifier(Modifier::BOLD);\\n35:     let desc_style = Style::default().fg(Color::White);\\n36: \\n37:     let lines: Vec<Line> = KEYBINDINGS\\n38:         .iter()\\n39:         .map(|(key, desc)| {\\n40:             Line::from(vec![\\n41:                 Span::styled(format!(\\\"  {:<12}\\\", key), key_style),\\n42:                 Span::styled(*desc, desc_style),\\n43:             ])\\n44:         })\\n45:         .collect();\\n46: \\n47:     let content_height = (lines.len() as u16) + 2; // +2 for borders\\n48:     let content_width = 40_u16;\\n49: \\n50:     let popup_height = content_height.min(area.height.saturating_sub(4));\\n51:     let popup_width = content_width.min(area.width.saturating_sub(4));\\n52: \\n53:     let x = area.x + (area.width.saturating_sub(popup_width)) / 2;\\n54:     let y = area.y + (area.height.saturating_sub(popup_height)) / 2;\\n55:     let popup_area = Rect::new(x, y, popup_width, popup_height);\\n56: \\n57:     frame.render_widget(Clear, popup_area);\\n58: \\n59:     let popup = Paragraph::new(lines).block(\\n60:         Block::default()\\n61:             .borders(Borders::ALL)\\n62:             .title(\\\"Help — Keybindings\\\")\\n63:             .border_style(Style::default().fg(Color::Cyan)),\\n64:     );\\n65:     frame.render_widget(popup, popup_area);\\n66: }\\n67: \\n68: #[cfg(test)]\\n69: mod tests {\\n70:     use super::*;\\n71: \\n72:     #[test]\\n73:     fn keybindings_is_non_empty() {\\n74:         assert!(!KEYBINDINGS.is_empty());\\n75:     }\\n76: \\n77:     #[test]\\n78:     fn keybindings_contains_help_toggle() {\\n79:         assert!(KEYBINDINGS.iter().any(|(key, _)| *key == \\\"?\\\"));\\n80:     }\\n81: \\n82:     #[test]\\n83:     fn keybindings_contains_quit() {\\n84:         assert!(KEYBINDINGS.iter().any(|(key, _)| *key == \\\"q\\\"));\\n85:     }\\n86: \\n87:     #[test]\\n88:     fn keybindings_have_descriptions() {\\n89:         for (key, desc) in KEYBINDINGS {\\n90:             assert!(!key.is_empty(), \\\"key should not be empty\\\");\\n91:             assert!(!desc.is_empty(), \\\"description should not be empty for key '{}'\\\", key);\\n92:         }\\n93:     }\\n94: \\n95:     #[test]\\n96:     fn render_does_not_panic() {\\n97:         use ratatui::{backend::TestBackend, Terminal};\\n98:         let backend = TestBackend::new(80, 24);\\n99:         let mut terminal = Terminal::new(backend).unwrap();\\n100:         terminal\\n101:             .draw(|frame| {\\n102:                 render(frame, frame.area());\\n103:             })\\n104:             .unwrap();\\n105:     }\\n106: \\n107:     #[test]\\n108:     fn render_handles_small_area() {\\n109:         use ratatui::{backend::TestBackend, Terminal};\\n110:         let backend = TestBackend::new(10, 5);\\n111:         let mut terminal = Terminal::new(backend).unwrap();\\n112:         terminal\\n113:             .draw(|frame| {\\n114:                 render(frame, frame.area());\\n115:             })\\n116:             .unwrap();\\n117:     }\\n118: }\"}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. The task is to make the `ProjectDetail` view work like `MyIssues` — pressing Enter on a project issue should open the `Detail` view, and Esc from that detail should go back to `ProjectDetail` (not `MyIssues`).\n\nThe key design decision: I need to track which list view the user came from when entering `Detail`. Currently, `back_to_list()` always goes to `MyIssues`, and `selected_issue()` always returns from the `my_issues` filtered list. I need to make the `Detail` view context-aware.\n\nLet me implement this:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_016CVnfEAgq6p93g2FS82zxz","name":"edit_file","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs","old_str":"pub enum View {\n    MyIssues,\n    ProjectList,\n    ProjectDetail,\n    Detail,\n}","new_str":"pub enum View {\n    MyIssues,\n    ProjectList,\n    ProjectDetail,\n    Detail,\n}\n\n/// Tracks which list view the user came from when entering the Detail view.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum DetailOrigin {\n    MyIssues,\n    ProjectDetail,\n}"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1899,"cache_read_input_tokens":89216,"output_tokens":364,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
