{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, the `selected_issue` change is tricky. It's used in many places, not just in Detail view. In `MyIssues` view, `selected_issue()` must still return from filtered issues regardless of `detail_origin`. The `detail_origin` only matters when we're in the `Detail` view. Let me rethink this.\n\nThe issue: `selected_issue()` is called from:\n1. `MyIssues` view / main loop for opening URLs, selecting etc.\n2. `Detail` view for rendering\n3. `main.rs` for getting issue identifier for threads\n\nThe cleanest approach: only use `detail_origin` in `selected_issue()` when the view is `Detail`. But `App` doesn't check `self.view` inside `selected_issue()`. Looking at the call sites:\n\n- In `main.rs` MyIssues context: `app.selected_issue()` is called before `app.select_issue()` (to get the id for threads), and also for `awaiting_open` handler. At that point `detail_origin` will still be whatever it was before.\n- In `Detail` view: `selected_issue()` is called during rendering.\n\nActually, since `detail_origin` is only set when entering Detail view, and when we're in MyIssues, the origin is always MyIssues (set during initialization or after last `select_issue()`). But if user goes: MyIssues → Detail → back → Projects → ProjectDetail → select project issue → Detail, then `detail_origin` would be `ProjectDetail`, and then backing out and going to MyIssues would have `detail_origin` still as `ProjectDetail`.\n\nThe cleanest approach: check the current view:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_01UjjDPaxAB6tai55viWZkSw","name":"edit_file","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs","old_str":"    pub fn selected_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\n        match self.detail_origin {\n            DetailOrigin::ProjectDetail => {\n                self.project_issues.get(self.project_issue_selected)\n            }\n            DetailOrigin::MyIssues => {\n                let issues = self.filtered_issues();\n                issues.get(self.selected).copied()\n            }\n        }\n    }","new_str":"    pub fn selected_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\n        if matches!(self.view, View::Detail) && self.detail_origin == DetailOrigin::ProjectDetail {\n            self.project_issues.get(self.project_issue_selected)\n        } else {\n            let issues = self.filtered_issues();\n            issues.get(self.selected).copied()\n        }\n    }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":580,"cache_read_input_tokens":93633,"output_tokens":701,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
