{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `selected_issue_url()` already uses `selected_issue()`, which now properly returns the project issue when in Detail view with ProjectDetail origin. Good.\n\nBut for the `awaiting_open` handler in main.rs, when we're in the `ProjectDetail` view (list, not detail), we need to handle it for project issues. Let me check how `awaiting_open` is set — it's a cross-view state. When the user presses `o` in ProjectDetail, `awaiting_open` becomes true, then the next key press checks the handler. The issue: the `awaiting_open` handler at the top of the event loop uses `app.selected_issue_url()` and `app.selected_issue()`, which in `ProjectDetail` view (not `Detail` view) returns from `filtered_issues()`. This needs fixing for the `o` → `l` flow in `ProjectDetail`.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the `awaiting_open` handler is a global handler (checked before view-specific handlers). So when the user is in `ProjectDetail` and presses `o` (which I just added), then presses `l`, the `awaiting_open` handler will try `app.selected_issue_url()`. Since view is `ProjectDetail`, `selected_issue()` returns from `filtered_issues()` (MyIssues), not project issues. Let me fix `selected_issue_url()` to also check the current view context:\n\nActually, I think a cleaner approach is to add a helper method that returns the \"contextually selected issue\" based on current view:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_019zWCgZWJuEw1q4ei8Z1pmf","name":"edit_file","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs","old_str":"    pub fn selected_issue_url(&self) -> Option<String> {\n        self.selected_issue().and_then(|i| i.url.clone())\n    }","new_str":"    pub fn selected_issue_url(&self) -> Option<String> {\n        self.context_issue().and_then(|i| i.url.clone())\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the issue relevant to the current view context.\n    /// In ProjectDetail or Detail-from-project, returns the selected project issue.\n    /// Otherwise, returns the selected my-issues issue.\n    pub fn context_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\n        match self.view {\n            View::ProjectDetail => self.selected_project_issue(),\n            View::Detail if self.detail_origin == DetailOrigin::ProjectDetail => {\n                self.selected_project_issue()\n            }\n            _ => {\n                let issues = self.filtered_issues();\n                issues.get(self.selected).copied()\n            }\n        }\n    }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":350,"cache_read_input_tokens":96941,"output_tokens":705,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_019zWCgZWJuEw1q4ei8Z1pmf","content":"{\"diff\":\"```diff\\nIndex: /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs\\n===================================================================\\n--- /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs\\toriginal\\n+++ /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs\\tmodified\\n@@ -416,11 +416,27 @@\\n         self.show_help = false;\\n     }\\n \\n     pub fn selected_issue_url(&self) -> Option<String> {\\n-        self.selected_issue().and_then(|i| i.url.clone())\\n+        self.context_issue().and_then(|i| i.url.clone())\\n     }\\n \\n+    /// Returns the issue relevant to the current view context.\\n+    /// In ProjectDetail or Detail-from-project, returns the selected project issue.\\n+    /// Otherwise, returns the selected my-issues issue.\\n+    pub fn context_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\\n+        match self.view {\\n+            View::ProjectDetail => self.selected_project_issue(),\\n+            View::Detail if self.detail_origin == DetailOrigin::ProjectDetail => {\\n+                self.selected_project_issue()\\n+            }\\n+            _ => {\\n+                let issues = self.filtered_issues();\\n+                issues.get(self.selected).copied()\\n+            }\\n+        }\\n+    }\\n+\\n     pub fn switch_to_projects(&mut self) {\\n         self.view = View::ProjectList;\\n     }\\n \\n```\",\"lineRange\":[419,437]}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update `selected_issue` to use `context_issue`:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_01DDRVTjsCCPyT4CndKqL3nG","name":"edit_file","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/app.rs","old_str":"    pub fn selected_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\n        if matches!(self.view, View::Detail) && self.detail_origin == DetailOrigin::ProjectDetail {\n            self.project_issues.get(self.project_issue_selected)\n        } else {\n            let issues = self.filtered_issues();\n            issues.get(self.selected).copied()\n        }\n    }","new_str":"    pub fn selected_issue(&self) -> Option<&Issue> {\n        self.context_issue()\n    }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1114,"cache_read_input_tokens":97291,"output_tokens":246,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff84-fd1e-7738-a45c-2a0f8dd421b5"}
